{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "By adapting pre-trained models to specific jobs, consistent outcomes and findings are achieved in the seq2seq code generation task [34][35][36][37].",
    "Deep learning techniques exhibit promise in generating code from natural language descriptions, offering benefits for complex domains while requiring less manual effort compared to treebased techniques [38].Various researchers have worked on code generation tasks using datasets such as CoNaLa, DJANGO, ATIS, Code-SearchNet, and others.",
    "Notable models and methods include Dong and Lapata's syntax-driven neural code generation [22], Yin and Neubig's reranking model [26], Shin et al. 's PATOIS [27], Sun et al.",
    "'s TreeGen [28], and Xu et al. 's deep learning model with external knowledge incorporation [29].In 2021, Dahal et al.",
    "conducted an analysis of treestructured architectures, evaluating text-to-tree, structured tree-to-tree, and linearized tree-to-tree models on constituencybased parse trees [18]."
  ],
